The South African Women’s football team beat neighbors Lesotho 1-0 in a second round African Women’s Cup of Nations qualifier in Maseru on Wednesday, thanks to an early goal from Leandra Smeda. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Women’s football team beat neighbors Lesotho 1-0 in a second round African Women’s Cup of Nations qualifier in Maseru on Wednesday, thanks to an early goal from Leandra Smeda. The win places coach Desiree Ellis’ side in a strong position to qualify for the African Cup of Nations, with the return leg against Lesotho scheduled to take place at the Dr Petrus Molemela Stadium in Bloemfontein on Sunday. The overall winner will automatically qualify for a place in the Women’s Afcon. The Women’s Afcon will be played in Ghana between 17 November and 1 December.